parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belts to retract properly can lead to serious injury or even death in the event of an accident, as the slack in the belts can cause the passenger to be thrown forward.
symptoms: The seat belts do not retract when there is slack
the seat belts do not lock into the receiver
the seat belts remain loose even after being pulled to lock into the receiver
the seat belts do not provide proper protection in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and plating issues on the wheels can cause slow air leaks, leading to unexplained flat tires, which can result in tire blowouts, accidents, and vehicle damage.
symptoms: peeling of plating on the wheels
corrosion between the tire and wheel
loosening of the seal between the tire and wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission malfunction can cause the vehicle's wheels to lock up, leading to an abrupt stop, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: the vehicle comes to an abrupt stop
